TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bera, Anil K.
AU  - Lee, Sangkyu
T1  - Information Matrix Test, Parameter Heterogeneity and ARCH: A Synthesis
PY  - 1993
Y1  - 1993/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297820
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 60
IS  - 1
SP  - 229
EP  - 240
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We apply the White information matrix (IM) test to the linear regression model with autocorrelated errors. A special case of one component of the test is found to be identical to the Engle Lagrange multiplier (LM) test for autoregressive conditional heteroskedasticity (ARCH). Given Chesher's interpretation of the IM test as a test for parameter heterogeneity, this establishes a connection among the IM test, ARCH and parameter variation. This also enables us to specify conditional heteroskedasticity in a more general and convenient way. Other interesting by-products of our analysis are tests for the variation in conditional and static skewness which we call tests for “heterocliticity”.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297820
ER  - 



