T1  - Smart Money, Noise Trading and Stock Price Behaviour
PY  - 1993
Y1  - 1993/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297810
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 60
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 34
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper estimates an equilibrium model of stock price behaviour in which changes in exponentially de-trended dividends and prices are normally distributed and exogenous “noise traders” interact with “smart-money” investors who have constant absolute risk aversion. The model can explain the volatility and predictability of U.S. stock returns in the period 1871–1986 using either a low discount rate (4% or below) and a large constant risk discount on the stock price, or a higher discount rate (5% or above) and noise trading correlated with fundamentals. The data are not well able to distinguish between these explanations.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297810
ER  - 



